article.headline: Morehead St. 84, Austin Peay 74
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Kenneth Faried scored 24 points and grabbed 17 rebounds to lead Morehead State to an 84-74 victory over Austin Peay on Saturday night. Maze Stallworth added 23 points for the Eagles (6-8, 3-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Robert Murry scored 14 points and Leon Buchanan finished with 10. Wes Channels scored 30 points for the Governors (6-7, 2-1). He shot 8-for-19, including 6-for-11 from 3-point range. Anthony Campbell contributed 16 points. The Eagles held a one-point lead midway through the second half, but went on an 11-1 run to take a 70-59 lead with 5:24 remaining. The Governors were outrebounded 37-21. Austin Peay also shot 53.8 percent from the free-throw line (14-for-26).
